---
title: Tender Hoisin Pork Stew & Garlic Rice with Carrot Salad & Coriander
description: Tonight’s slow-cooked supper boasts savoury Asian flavours, with pork scotch fillet cooked in a rich hoisin sauce until fall-apart tender. A refreshing carrot salad is the perfect accompaniment to balance it out, with a helping of garlic rice to soak up all the sauce.

*This recipe is under 650kcal per serving.*
